e, I should stay silent rather than send a notification about what looks like a natural completion rather than a new change. I'm reviewing the full session list to get a complete picture of what's currently active versus what was reported earlier. Comparing my current view against the 09:15 snapshot, the only real change is that cron:e7885813 has completed since then, while everything else remains stable—no new failures, no fresh sessions spawned, and no blockers have emerged. The DTLX cron that triggered this check ran as expected, so there's nothing new to report to the group.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Silent exit — no changes detected since last report.\\n\\n**09:15 UTC state (reported):** 4 active sessions — `cron:ed2d0b5d`, `cron:6f3323ef`, `cron:e7885813`, `telegram:group:-5163901258`\\n**09:44 UTC (now):** 4 active sessions — `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅, `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ (running this run), `cron:e7885813` done (natural completion ~08:49 UTC — pre-existing), `telegram:group:-5163901258` ✅\\n\\nNo new failures. No new sessions. No new blockers. Pipeline stable.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 30023,\n            \"output\": 581,\n            \"totalTokens\": 44986,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 438,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776159879505,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d3f886d500b8c8874a31b373d9406\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"5ce78280\",\n            \"seq\": 5\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webcha